Sec. 13.112. TESTS FOR STATE INSTITUTIONS. As requested by the
comptroller or the governing body of a state institution, the
department shall test each weighing or measuring device used by a
state institution for any purpose, including a weighing or measuring
device used in checking the receipt and distribution of supplies.
The department shall report results of the test to the chairman of
the governing body of the institution.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1033, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by Acts 1989, 71st Leg., ch. 230, Sec. 23, eff. Sept. 1,
1989.
Amended by:
Acts 2007, 80th Leg., R.S., Ch. 937 (H.B. 3560), Sec. 1.80, eff.
September 1, 2007.
Acts 2009, 81st Leg., R.S., Ch. 913 (H.B. 2925), Sec. 12, eff.
September 1, 2009.

